// Build-time secrets for the Still app targets.
//
// This tracked file declares each key with an EMPTY default so a fresh clone builds (RevenueCat just
// won't configure). Real values live in Secrets.local.xcconfig (gitignored), pulled in by the
// optional include below — a missing local file is not an error (#include? vs #include). The keys
// surface to Swift via Info.plist substitution ($(REVENUECAT_PUBLIC_API_KEY)).
//
// To set your key locally:  echo 'REVENUECAT_PUBLIC_API_KEY = appl_xxx' > Config/Secrets.local.xcconfig
//
// Only the RevenueCat PUBLIC (appl_) key belongs here — it is a client-side publishable key. The
// SECRET (sk_) key and the webhook token are backend-only (Supabase) and must never reach the app.

REVENUECAT_PUBLIC_API_KEY =

#include? "Secrets.local.xcconfig"
